## Assumptions being carried forward

| Assumption | Risk if wrong | How to verify |
|---|---|---|
| `.b` folder name is unique enough to serve as the batch business key | Low — naming is instrument-generated and timestamp-anchored | Confirm with analyst that folder names are never reused for different batches |
| `.d` folder name is unique within a scan (timestamp structure prevents collisions) | Low | Confirm with analyst; verify no duplicate `.d` folder names exist in real batch data |
| `target.rp` contains one record per compound (not multiple rows per compound) | Medium — if there are multiple rows, compound de-duplication logic is needed | Verify against sample files before parser implementation |
| All three U-Del variants (`U-Delete`, `U-Del`, `UDEL`) are exhaustive | Medium — if additional variants exist, they will be silently missed | Confirm with analyst; add ability to flag "unknown comment values" in parse output |
| A few hundred `.d` folders is the upper bound for v1 batch sizes | Low — confirmed by project owner | Re-verify before scaling to larger data sets |

